Files:
- platform/mcp-server/src/plugin-management.ts (PluginSearchResult type + searchNpmPlugins + fetchAllPlugins + probeDirectPackage)
- platform/browser-extension/src/side-panel/bridge.ts (PluginSearchResult type)

Context:
The PluginSearchResult type is defined independently in two places (not in shared). Both must be updated in lockstep.

The npm search API (/-/v1/search) does NOT return custom package.json fields — only name, description, version, publisher. To get opentabs.iconSvg and opentabs.iconDarkSvg, we must fetch full package metadata from /<package>/latest for each result.

The current searchNpmPlugins function (line 250) orchestrates two parallel fetches: fetchAllPlugins (paginated search API) and probeDirectPackage (exact match). Both return NpmRegistrySearchPackage which only has name, description, version, publisher.

Changes:

1. Update PluginSearchResult (line 31-37 in plugin-management.ts):
```typescript
interface PluginSearchResult {
  name: string;
  displayName: string;
  description: string;
  version: string;
  author: string;
  iconSvg: string;
  iconDarkSvg: string;
}
```

2. Update NpmRegistrySearchPackage (line 177-182) to add optional icon fields:
```typescript
interface NpmRegistrySearchPackage {
  name: string;
  description?: string;
  version: string;
  publisher?: { username?: string };
  iconSvg?: string;
  iconDarkSvg?: string;
}
```

3. After the search + filter + merge phase in searchNpmPlugins (around line 275-300), add a batch fetch phase that fetches /<package>/latest for each result to retrieve icon data. Use Promise.all with individual try/catch so one failed fetch doesn't break the whole search. Something like:
```typescript
const withIcons = await Promise.all(
  results.map(async (result) => {
    try {
      const resp = await fetch(`${NPM_REGISTRY}/${result.name}/latest`, { signal: controller.signal });
      if (!resp.ok) return result;
      const data = await resp.json() as { opentabs?: { iconSvg?: string; iconDarkSvg?: string } };
      return {
        ...result,
        iconSvg: data.opentabs?.iconSvg ?? '',
        iconDarkSvg: data.opentabs?.iconDarkSvg ?? '',
      };
    } catch {
      return result;
    }
  })
);
return withIcons;
```

4. For probeDirectPackage (line 211-239), it already fetches the full packument from /<package>. Extend the response type and extract opentabs.iconSvg and opentabs.iconDarkSvg from the latest version's metadata. Note: probeDirectPackage fetches the full packument (all versions), not /<package>/latest. The opentabs field is in the root of each version's package.json, accessible via data.versions[latest]. Update the data type cast at line 222-227 to include opentabs, and extract icons at line 230-235.

5. Update the bridge.ts PluginSearchResult type (line 29-35) to match.

Constraints:
- Do NOT move PluginSearchResult to shared — keep the two independent definitions.
- The icon fetch must not slow down the search when icons are unavailable — use try/catch per-package.
- All 115 plugins currently on npm are published by opentabs-dev-admin. No backwards compatibility needed — iconSvg and iconDarkSvg are required (non-optional) string fields on PluginSearchResult. Use empty string as the default when a plugin has no icons.
- The AbortController signal must be threaded through to icon fetch requests.
- Do NOT change the NpmPluginCard or PluginIcon components in this story.
